---AGGREGATE FUNCTIONS---
- COUNT() counts the number of occurrences of a value(or number of rows) in a specified column
    - ex: SELECT COUNT(*)
          from film;
    - ex: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT(rating))
          FROM film;

- SUM() adds up values in the specified function
    - ex: SELECT SUM(length)
          FROM film;

- AVG() returns the average of a value from a specified column
    - SELECT AVG(rental_rate)
      FROM film
      WHERE rating = "G";

- MIN() or MAX() finds the min or max value
    - ex: SELECT MIN(length)
          FROM film;
    - ex: SELECT MAX(length)
          FROM film;